  <li>MSDN blog post from 2016:<a href="https://blogs.msdn.microsoft.com/commandline/2016/11/17/do-not-change-linux-files-using-windows-apps-and-tools/">DO NOT, under ANY circumstances, create and/or modify Linux files using Windows apps, tools, scripts, consoles, etc.</a>:
    <ul>
      <li>Reading files from Windows on Linux is OK</li>
      <li>Copying files from Windows to Linux is OK</li>
      <li><strong>Editing Linux files or modifying Linux files on Windows is NOT OK</strong> &lt;â€“ testing jekyll on mac versus jekyll on windows subsystem for linux</li>
    </ul>
